with a bad review...

651
00:46:59,888 --> 00:47:02,356
and I was there
visiting Dionne Warwick.

652
00:47:03,858 --> 00:47:06,261
He thought he was Dionne Warwick.

653
00:47:06,261 --> 00:47:10,431
- Who is Dionne Warwick?
- Sacrilege, darling.

654
00:47:10,431 --> 00:47:12,100
She's Whitney Houston's aunt.

655
00:47:12,100 --> 00:47:14,402
She's very good
on the Psychic Friends Network.

656
00:47:14,402 --> 00:47:19,271
- Isn't she?
- Do you know the way to San Jose

657
00:47:25,413 --> 00:47:28,583
There I was with Dionne.
His real name, by the way, is Jerry.

658
00:47:28,583 --> 00:47:32,086
We were having a sing-along,
then suddenly...

659
00:47:32,086 --> 00:47:35,924
breezing through the doors
from the shock therapy room...

660
00:47:35,924 --> 00:47:37,592
I saw her.

661
00:47:37,592 --> 00:47:40,220
A vision in pink.

662
00:47:42,430 --> 00:47:45,099
- You don't wear pink.
- She does.

663
00:47:45,099 --> 00:47:47,602
Sometimes she does wear pink.

664
00:47:47,602 --> 00:47:50,371
- You do.
- I do.

665
00:47:50,371 --> 00:47:52,640
l said to Dionne...

666
00:47:52,640 --> 00:47:56,077
''Dionne, who is this vision?

667
00:47:56,077 --> 00:47:59,948
Surely, she must be the understudy
to some fabulous Broadway star.

668
00:47:59,948 --> 00:48:02,450
Look at her skin.
Who does her hair?''

669
00:48:02,450 --> 00:48:05,353
- In that moment, I knew.
- We don't all need to know--

670
00:48:05,353 --> 00:48:06,786
We do!

671
00:48:10,458 --> 00:48:14,128
- I'm very curious.
- They do.

672
00:48:14,128 --> 00:48:16,631
I knew...

673
00:48:16,631 --> 00:48:19,300
