00:54:46,620 --> 00:54:49,612
alone together, you know?

744
00:54:52,226 --> 00:54:54,762
Except for that hot affair
we'll have twice a year.

745
00:54:54,762 --> 00:54:56,696
Except for that.

746
00:55:04,205 --> 00:55:09,176
I mean, you commit
to this wedding...

747
00:55:09,176 --> 00:55:13,881
and then it seems
like there's this momentum...

748
00:55:13,881 --> 00:55:16,441
and then you forget
you chose it.

749
00:55:22,189 --> 00:55:24,425
You and I didn't--

750
00:55:24,425 --> 00:55:28,896
In our relationships
with other people...

751
00:55:28,896 --> 00:55:33,333
we didn't use
the word love a lot, did we?

752
00:55:36,470 --> 00:55:39,540
Kimmy says
it you love someone...

753
00:55:39,540 --> 00:55:42,109
you say it.

754
00:55:42,109 --> 00:55:44,270
You say it right then,
out loud.

755
00:55:45,579 --> 00:55:49,683
Otherwise,
the moment just--

756
00:55:49,683 --> 00:55:51,617
Passes you by.

757
00:56:14,175 --> 00:56:16,109
We don't even have a song.

758
00:56:17,411 --> 00:56:21,438
Kimmy and I don't have a song.

759
00:56:22,917 --> 00:56:24,885
Do you think that's a bad sign?

760
00:56:28,622 --> 00:56:30,724
Someday

761
00:56:30,724 --> 00:56:33,727
When I'm awfully low

762
00:56:33,727 --> 00:56:36,096
And the world is cold

763
00:56:36,096 --> 00:56:40,658
l will feel a glow
just thinking of you

764
00:56:42,536 --> 00:56:47,667
And the way you look tonight

765
00:56:48,542 --> 00:56:50,811
Is your dance card tilled?

766
00:56:50,811 --> 00:56:54,181
I'd have to check.
I keep it on Powerbook these days.

767
00:56:54,181 --> 00:56:56,115
Is that right?

768
00:56:59,253 --> 00:57:01,255
With each word

769
00:57:01,255 --> 00:57:04,247
Your tenderness grows

770
00:57:05,659 --> 00:57:09,652
Tearing my fears apart

771
00:57:11,765 --> 00:57:16,704
With each laugh
that wrinkles your nose

772
00:57:16,704 --> 00:57:20,538
Touches my foolish heart

773
00:57:59,346 --> 00:58:00,779
Excuse me.

774
00:58:04,218 --> 00:58:07,555
- I thought Michael was picking me up.
- I said I'd drop you at the stag.

775
00:58:07,555 --> 00:58:10,724
He's got a lot to do.
I'm the unofficial best man.

776
00:58:10,724 --> 00:58:13,294
Of course.

777
00:58:13,294 --> 00:58:18,299
Kim said when Michael turned the job
down that there was no friction.

778
00:58:18,299 --> 00:58:20,434
Friction? No.

779
00:58:20,434 --> 00:58:22,269
Good.

780
00:58:22,269 --> 00:58:25,072
I haven't caused a problem,
have I?

781
00:58:25,072 --> 00:58:27,404
You haven't. Nobody has.

782
00:58:29,076 --> 00:58:31,879
Listen,
you're just a little bit early.

783
00:58:31,879 --> 00:58:33,881
Actually, I needed
to make some phone calls.

784
00:58:33,881 --> 00:58:36,650
- Is it possible to use your office?
- of course.

785
00:58:36,650 --> 00:58:39,175
- At the end of the hall on the left.
- Thank you.

786
00:58:40,654 --> 00:58:42,952
Take your time.

787
00:58:50,764 --> 00:58:52,698
E-mall.

788
00:58:53,901 --> 00:58:57,234
''File'' ''New Letter'' ''Open'' ''Close''
New letter.

789
00:59:03,777 --> 00:59:08,382
To: Eric Isaacson...

790
00:59:08,382 --> 00:59:14,321
''Mall Out''
Senior editor, Sport Magazine.

791
00:59:14,321 --> 00:59:18,087
From: Walter Wallace.

792
00:59:20,160 --> 00:59:23,964
You can do this. It's easy.
Just do it fast, get it over with.

793
00:59:23,964 --> 00:59:25,898
It's like it never happened.

794
00:59:27,301 --> 00:59:31,105
Eric, I need a favor.

795
00:59:31,105 --> 00:59:35,409
My daughter's
every happiness...

796
00:59:35,409 --> 00:59:37,244
is in your hands.

797
00:59:37,244 --> 00:59:41,215
I have offered Mike O'Neal...

798
00:59:41,215 --> 00:59:43,917
my new son-in-Law...

799
00:59:43,917 --> 00:59:46,720
a great opportunity...

800
00:59:46,720 --> 00:59:48,922
in my company.

801
00:59:48,922 --> 00:59:52,426
To his own detriment...

802
00:59:52,426 --> 00:59:54,428
Michael will not...

803
00:59:54,428 --> 00:59:58,432
accept our offer...

804
00:59:58,432 --> 01:00:02,266
while he works for you.

805
01:00:26,994 --> 01:00:30,431
My daughter joins me
in this plea...

806
01:00:30,431 --> 01:00:34,101
for your cooperation.

807
01:00:34,101 --> 01:00:38,338
With gratitude, Walter.

808
01:00:38,338 --> 01:00:40,306
''Do You Wish To Send?''
''Yes'' ''No''

809
01:00:41,475 --> 01:00:44,569
Why would I send this?
He'd get tired.

810
01:00:47,281 --> 01:00:49,010
''Save For Later'' ''Delete''

811
01:00:52,853 --> 01:00:54,286
Save for later.

812
01:00:59,393 --> 01:01:01,261
It's not like I'm sending it.

813
01:01:01,261 --> 01:01:04,231
I'm just saving it
for a few hours...

814
01:01:04,231 --> 01:01:07,101
till we come back here and...

815
01:01:07,101 --> 01:01:08,936
Michael can see it.

816
01:01:08,936 --> 01:01:11,268
Perfectly harmless.

817
01:01:50,744 --> 01:01:52,177
''Wallace Company''

818
01:02:03,590 --> 01:02:07,094
Send out this, this,
not this, this.

819
01:02:07,094 --> 01:02:09,062
That's it.

820
01:02:09,062 --> 01:02:13,600
I'm holding tour or five e-malls
I wrote over lunch. Send those too.

821
01:02:13,600 --> 01:02:17,004
- Yes, sir.
- Bye.

822
01:02:17,004 --> 01:02:18,904
all set?

823
01:02:20,340 --> 01:02:22,910
I can't believe this!
Did you try every key?

824
01:02:22,910 --> 01:02:25,312
It's no big deal.
She just gave us the wrong keys.

825
01:02:25,312 --> 01:02:29,283
There's got to be a janitor
or a guard...

826
01:02:29,283 --> 01:02:32,853
or a cleaning woman
or, you know, some kind of--

827
01:02:32,853 --> 01:02:37,658
Somebody has to be in this building!
I need a brick.

828
01:02:37,658 --> 01:02:39,956
What's the big deal
about getting this tile tonight?

829
01:02:41,428 --> 01:02:43,797
- I'm up against a deadline.
- Me too.

830
01:02:43,797 --> 01:02:46,733
- I'm getting married tomorrow.
- That's my point!

831
01:02:46,733 --> 01:02:49,169
Everybody will be busy
with more important things...

832
01:02:49,169 --> 01:02:51,738
and this is really my last chance.

833
01:02:51,738 --> 01:02:54,775
If I could just get up to Walter's
office, they're by the computer.

834
01:02:54,775 --> 01:02:58,111
Then I could just e-mail
those figures right out now!

835
01:02:58,111 --> 01:02:59,880
Tomorrow's Sunday.

836
01:02:59,880 --> 01:03:01,949
Nobody's doing business.

837
01:03:01,949 --> 01:03:06,477
Monday morning, crack of dawn,
Walter will walk you right up there.

838
01:03:07,788 --> 01:03:09,722
Give it up, kid.

839
01:03:11,291 --> 01:03:12,724
Can't win them all.

840
01:03:26,740 --> 01:03:28,173
Good night.

841
01:03:36,683 --> 01:03:40,449
This thing mean
that much to you?

842
01:03:43,023 --> 01:03:45,192
We'll use the phone
in your room.

843
01:03:45,192 --> 01:03:47,527
Walter's probably not even asleep.

844
01:03:47,527 --> 01:03:50,530
- I'll drive you up there.
- Thank you !

845
01:03:50,530 --> 01:03:53,834
We'll get the right key,
and we'll go back to the office.

846
01:03:53,834 --> 01:03:56,603
If I fall asleep on the altar tomorrow,
you'd better be there.

847
01:03:56,603 --> 01:03:58,505
I'll be there.

848
01:03:58,505 --> 01:04:03,677
These are all from Eric.
This fax is from Eric too.

849
01:04:03,677 --> 01:04:06,246
My wedding. You'd think my boss
would leave me alone.

850
01:04:06,246 --> 01:04:08,180
Maybe it's Congratulations.

851
01:04:18,959 --> 01:04:20,688
What is it?

852
01:04:27,501 --> 01:04:30,604
''Mike, I can't believe I'm doing this to
you on the night before your wedding...

853
01:04:30,604 --> 01:04:34,908
but I think you need
and deserve...

854
01:04:34,908 --> 01:04:36,842
to know what
you're marrying into.

855
01:04:41,148 --> 01:04:44,709
I received the following e-mall
this afternoon:

856
01:04:46,420 --> 01:04:49,878
'Eric, I need a favor.
My daughter's every--'''

857
01:04:52,059 --> 01:04:54,461
Isabelle, I need to talk to Kim.

858
01:04:54,461 --> 01:04:56,997
- Is anything wrong?
- No, I'm just tired.

859
01:04:56,997 --> 01:04:59,693
Please put her on.
Thanks.

860
01:05:03,236 --> 01:05:05,170
could you give me a minute?

861
01:05:06,974 --> 01:05:08,407
Please?

862
01:05:56,323 --> 01:05:59,121
Excuse me, miss.
Are you locked out?

863
01:06:02,396 --> 01:06:05,797
Just stepped out.
It's a no-smoking room.

864
01:06:08,168 --> 01:06:10,404
It's a nonsmoking floor too.

865
01:06:10,404 --> 01:06:14,207
Maybe you could go down
to the lobby.

866
01:06:14,207 --> 01:06:16,232
Why don't you have me arrested?

867
01:06:18,478 --> 01:06:20,113
I mean it.

868
01:06:20,113 --> 01:06:23,810
I am a dangerous, criminal person.

869
01:06:26,186 --> 01:06:28,814
I do bad things
to honest people.

870
01:06:31,258 --> 01:06:33,960
You can make a citizen's arrest.
I wouldn't struggle.

871
01:06:33,960 --> 01:06:36,451
It'd be like getting AI Capone
on tax evasion.

872
01:06:44,938 --> 01:06:47,168
Can I help you, miss?

873
01:06:52,479 --> 01:06:54,640
Do you smoke, Richard?

874
01:06:55,382 --> 01:06:57,951
Yes, I do, but--

875
01:06:57,951 --> 01:06:59,748
It's a nonsmoking floor.

876
01:07:02,989 --> 01:07:04,923
But you know what?

877
01:07:26,913 --> 01:07:32,249
You know,
my grandmother always said...

878
01:07:34,354 --> 01:07:37,323
''This too shall pass.''

879
01:07:40,727 --> 01:07:42,160
Thanks, Richard.

880
01:08:07,654 --> 01:08:10,991
l want you to quit this shit.

881
01:08:10,991 --> 01:08:12,424
It'll kill you.

882
01:08:16,963 --> 01:08:18,396
What happened?

883
01:08:20,934 --> 01:08:23,803
It's over.
She denied it.

884
01:08:23,803 --> 01:08:26,740
She said
I was crazy and paranoid.

885
01:08:26,740 --> 01:08:29,776
A bad combination.

886
01:08:29,776 --> 01:08:31,311
There's a big...

887
01:08:31,311 --> 01:08:35,015
brunch tomorrow morning
at her parents' house.

888
01:08:35,015 --> 01:08:37,779
She said,
''How could I call it oft?

889
01:08:40,086 --> 01:08:42,077
What am I supposed
to tell everyone?''

890
01:08:43,857 --> 01:08:46,189
It's for the best.
It really is.

891
01:08:47,027 --> 01:08:48,961
She was right.

892
01:08:51,164 --> 01:08:53,132
I am crazy...

893
01:08:55,635 --> 01:08:58,126
to tall for someone
I hardly knew.

894
01:09:03,443 --> 01:09:05,343
I'm so glad you're here.

895
01:09:12,485 --> 01:09:15,750
Have you still got that ring?

896
01:09:27,167 --> 01:09:30,000
I tried it on,
and it won't come off.

897
01:10:08,475 --> 01:10:12,536
Why don't we take a walk
or have some food sent up?

898
01:10:15,415 --> 01:10:17,651
I just want to be alone.

899
01:10:17,651 --> 01:10:19,986
Is that okay?

900
01:10:19,986 --> 01:10:21,419
Sure.

901
01:10:24,524 --> 01:10:29,663
Maybe I'll go back to New York
for awhile and hang with you.

902
01:10:29,663 --> 01:10:34,467
Eric will understand.
Or we could go somewhere...

903
01:10:34,467 --> 01:10:35,900
if you want.

904
01:10:37,370 --> 01:10:40,066
''If San Antonio
sweeps Sacramento--''

905
01:10:41,508 --> 01:10:43,442
I've never been to Texas.

906
01:11:32,525 --> 01:11:34,459
''Brown''

907
01:11:53,380 --> 01:11:54,813
You what?

908
01:12:17,470 --> 01:12:19,495
- Can I try that?
- Sure.

909
01:12:30,283 --> 01:12:32,342
- Excuse me.
- Good Luck.

910
01:12:35,488 --> 01:12:37,791
So this is your basic
call-off-the-wedding party?

911
01:12:37,791 --> 01:12:41,494
I came here to confront everybody.
I won't slink away like some coward.

912
01:12:41,494 --> 01:12:44,264
Besides, she hasn't told anyone.
l don't know what I'm supposed to do.

913
01:12:44,264 --> 01:12:48,360
There is a wedding at 6:00.

914
01:12:55,141 --> 01:13:00,340
Have you changed your mind?
Do you want to marry Kimmy?

915
01:13:03,616 --> 01:13:07,143
I made a decision.
It's over.

916
01:13:09,055 --> 01:13:10,989
I'll go tell them.

917
01:13:13,159 --> 01:13:17,255
First,
do you think she's all right?

918
01:13:18,198 --> 01:13:20,393
could you
check on her for me?

919
01:13:24,304 --> 01:13:27,296
These are the most beautiful flowers
I've ever seen.

920
01:13:31,044 --> 01:13:32,477
How is he?

921
01:13:35,248 --> 01:13:37,917
He's sort of wondering...

922
01:13:37,917 --> 01:13:41,216
why you haven't told your parents
that the wedding's oft.

923
01:13:42,856 --> 01:13:46,626
I don't know. I'm still hoping
for a miracle, I suppose.

924
01:13:46,626 --> 01:13:50,196
How could he think that
my father and I would do such a thing?

925
01:13:50,196 --> 01:13:53,290
I only minored in psych,
you understand, but...

926
01:13:55,068 --> 01:13:58,238
maybe Michael couldn't commit
to this marriage...

927
01:13:58,238 --> 01:14:00,974
so he created...

928
01:14:00,974 --> 01:14:02,475
a delusion...

929
01:14:02,475 --> 01:14:05,445
produced an unconscious,
psychosomatic...

930
01:14:05,445 --> 01:14:07,379
manifestation of--

931
01:14:10,116 --> 01:14:11,708
I'm better with food.

932
01:14:14,254 --> 01:14:18,892
You're Michael.
You're in a fancy French restaurant.

933
01:14:18,892 --> 01:14:22,295
You order...

934
01:14:22,295 --> 01:14:24,388
crème brulee for dessert.

935
01:14:25,465 --> 01:14:28,301
It's beautiful. It's sweet.

936
01:14:28,301 --> 01:14:32,038
It's irritatingly perfect.

937
01:14:32,038 --> 01:14:34,707
Suddenly, Michael realizes...

938
01:14:34,707 --> 01:14:37,443
he doesn't want crème brulee.

939
01:14:37,443 --> 01:14:42,278
- He wants something else.
- What does he want?

940
01:14:44,584 --> 01:14:47,314
- Jell-O.
- ''Jell-O''?

941
01:14:48,521 --> 01:14:52,892
- Why Jell-O?
- He's comfortable with Jell-O.

942
01:14:52,892 --> 01:14:56,195
Jell-O makes him comfortable.

943
01:14:56,195 --> 01:14:58,398
I realize
compared to crème brulee...

944
01:14:58,398 --> 01:15:01,367
it's Jell-O,
but maybe that's what he needs.

945
01:15:03,403 --> 01:15:04,961
I could be Jell-O.

946
01:15:06,606 --> 01:15:09,275
Crème brulee
can never be Jell-O.

947
01:15:09,275 --> 01:15:12,045
You could never be Jell-O.

948
01:15:12,045 --> 01:15:15,315
- I have to be Jell-O.
- You'll never be Jell-O.

949
01:15:15,315 --> 01:15:20,520
Tell your parents. lf you're waiting
for that ''do you take this man'' part...

950
01:15:20,520 --> 01:15:22,715
- it's considered poor form.
- I love him.

951
01:15:23,923 --> 01:15:26,326
Whatever delusions
I drove Michael to...

952
01:15:26,326 --> 01:15:28,328
there's truth
at the heart of it.

953
01:15:28,328 --> 01:15:31,664
I want him to work
for my father.

954
01:15:31,664 --> 01:15:34,827
I want to stay in school,
and I want a life of my own.

955
01:15:36,035 --> 01:15:39,801
Please, tell him it's my fault
and I love him.

956
01:15:41,240 --> 01:15:43,538
You're the only person
that I trust.

957
01:15:49,616 --> 01:15:52,346
- I'll be right back.
- Thank you.

958
01:16:05,465 --> 01:16:07,667
How is she?

959
01:16:07,667 --> 01:16:11,034
- Knock it off!
- Yes, sir!

960
01:16:13,039 --> 01:16:15,441
- I asked you--
- She admits that it's her fault.

961
01:16:15,441 --> 01:16:18,069
Totally, completely,
inexcusably her fault.

962
01:16:21,481 --> 01:16:23,449
Do you think
she still loves me?

963
01:16:26,886 --> 01:16:30,490
Love is a strong word...

964
01:16:30,490 --> 01:16:33,059
and I don't know that
I'm necessarily qualified--

965
01:16:33,059 --> 01:16:37,163
I guess I wouldn't be totally oft base
it I said that, in her way...

966
01:16:37,163 --> 01:16:39,961
she does possess
strong feelings--

967
01:16:45,705 --> 01:16:47,639
Sure, she does.

968
01:16:48,541 --> 01:16:50,543
She's crazy about you.

969
01:16:50,543 --> 01:16:54,570
You fill up my senses

970
01:16:55,548 --> 01:16:59,211
Like a night in the forest

971
01:17:00,653 --> 01:17:06,059
Like the mountains
in springtime

972
01:17:06,059 --> 01:17:08,728
Like a walk in the rain

973
01:17:08,728 --> 01:17:11,060
Tell her I'll marry her
at 6:00...

974
01:17:12,131 --> 01:17:14,065
it she'll still have me.

975
01:17:16,302 --> 01:17:18,133
Please.

976
01:17:19,639 --> 01:17:24,210
Like a sleepy blue ocean

977
01:17:24,210 --> 01:17:27,202
I'll be right back.

978
01:17:31,651 --> 01:17:36,679
Come love me again

979
01:17:47,900 --> 01:17:49,834
What did he say?

980
01:17:55,508 --> 01:17:56,941
He said...

981
01:18:00,480 --> 01:18:01,913
''Marry me.''

982
01:18:06,552 --> 01:18:10,156
Thank God you were here.

983
01:18:10,156 --> 01:18:12,358
I got so contused.

984
01:18:12,358 --> 01:18:13,791
It happens.

985
01:18:14,961 --> 01:18:16,394
Got a minute?

986
01:18:18,431 --> 01:18:19,864
What's up?

987
01:18:31,577 --> 01:18:34,847
I have to say this quick or I'll
just have this massive coronary...

988
01:18:34,847 --> 01:18:37,984
and then you'll never hear it,
and you have to.

989
01:18:37,984 --> 01:18:42,955
This is, by far, the dumbest thing
I've ever done in my entire life.

990
01:18:42,955 --> 01:18:48,361
So dumb, in fact, that I can't.
But I'm gonna.

991
01:18:48,361 --> 01:18:49,885
What's wrong?

992
01:18:57,603 --> 01:19:01,140
I love you.
I've loved you for nine years.

993
01:19:01,140 --> 01:19:05,545
I've just been too arrogant
and scared to realize it.

994
01:19:05,545 --> 01:19:07,780
Now I'm just scared.

995
01:19:07,780 --> 01:19:11,651
I realize this comes
at a very inopportune time...

